<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1260,2005]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1260,1285]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Body length 
<quantity box="[522,626,1260,1284]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.22" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" unit="mm" value="3.22">3.22 mm</quantity>
. Color: body castaneous. Head (
<figureCitation box="[992,1061,1260,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1512,1535]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1489]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Dissomphalus spp., ♂, head, dorsal view, except 2 lateral view. 1 – 2. D. isteus sp. nov. 3. D. azagus sp. nov. 4. D. asfartus sp. nov. 5. D. iozus sp. nov. 6. D. asitius sp. nov. 7. D. ibocius sp. nov. 8. D. tisinus sp. nov. 9. D. ardonius sp. nov. 10. D. arteus sp. nov. 11. D. ettus sp. nov. 12. D. ibrastus sp. nov.. Scale bars = 20 µm, except fig. 10 = 50 µm and fig. 4 = 100 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1010016/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Mandible with two distal teeth. Median clypeal lobe trapezoidal, with one angulate tooth; median clypeal carina high in profile, complete or nearly so, straight in profile or nearly so. Frons weakly coriaceous and punctures small. Vertex crest weakly concave. Pronotal disc coriaceous; anterior margin coarse. Metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[838,922,1367,1392]" captionStart="FIGURES 33 – 44" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1907,1930]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,553,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,553,1886]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 33 – 44. Dissomphalus spp., ♂, metasomal tergal process, dorsal view. 33. D. isteus sp. nov. 34. D. azagus sp. nov. 35. D. asfartus sp. nov. 36. D. iozus sp. nov. 37. D. asitius sp. nov. 38. D. ibocius sp. nov. 39. D. tisinus sp. nov. 40. D. ardonius sp. nov. 41. D. arteus sp. nov. 42. D. ettus sp. nov. 43. D. ibrastus sp. nov. 44. D. racarus sp. nov.. Scale bars = 20 µm, except fig. 35 = 200 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1010022/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). Tergal process with lateral, shallow, circular and small depression, with large, very low and dorsad tubercle placed on center of depression, pit large, with short and sparse tuft of setae. Posterior hypopygeal margin median straight with angled corners (
<figureCitation box="[1166,1249,1439,1464]" captionStart="FIGURES 64 – 75" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1938,1961]" captionTargetBox="[175,1408,606,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,569,1917]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 64 – 75. Dissomphalus spp., ♂, hypopygium, internal view. 64. D. isteus sp. nov. 65. D. azagus sp. nov. 66. D. asfartus sp. nov. 67. D. iozus sp. nov. 68. D. asitius sp. nov. 69. D. ibocius sp. nov. 70. D. tisinus sp. nov. 71. D. ardonius sp. nov. 72. D. arteus sp. nov. 73. D. ettus sp. nov. 74. D. ibrastus sp. nov. 75. D. racarus sp. nov.. Scale bars = 125 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1010028/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 123 – 135" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1820,1843]" captionTargetBox="[170,1430,415,1784]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,411,1799]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 123 – 135. Dissomphalus spp., ♂, genitália. 123 – 124. D. angulatus 123. Ventral view. 124. Lateral view. 125 – 126. D. asitius sp. nov. 125. Dorsal view. 126. Ventral view. 127 – 128. D. ibocius sp. nov. 127. Dorsal view. 128. Ventral view. 129 – 130. D. tisinus sp. nov. 129. Dorsal view. 130. Ventral view. 131 – 132. D. cervoides 131. Dorsal view. 132. Ventral view. 133 – 135. D. ardonius sp. nov. 133. Dorsal view. 134. Ventral view. 135. Lateral view. Scale bars = 250 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1010038/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Figs 133–135</figureCitation>
): paramere with dorsal margin entirely wide; apical margin truncate. Aedeagal ventral ramus shorter than dorsal body, entirely wide, cross section laminar; surface vertical; inner margin strongly sinuous; outer margin slightly sinuous; apex long, slightly crenulate, parallel; additional inner ramus long; basal stub long and narrow. Aedeagal dorsal body with two pairs of apical lobes, outer lobe long, vertical and very narrow, with apical margin acute and ventrad; inner pair stout, membranous and setose. Apodeme not extending beyond genital ring.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1260,2005]" box="[199,636,1655,1680]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1655,1680]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Variation.</emphasis>
Metasoma light castaneous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1260,2005]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1692,1717]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is easily recognized by having two spines in the ventral margin of the apical lobes of the aedeagal dorsal body with apical spine shorter than distal one, the aedeagal ventral ramus vertical and wide in the median portion with wavy apex. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Azevedo, 2017" authorityName="Azevedo" authorityYear="2017" box="[866,985,1765,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Dissomphalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urazius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[866,985,1765,1788]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">D. urazius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[994,1085,1764,1789]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[994,1085,1764,1789]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
by having spine in the ventral margin of apical lobes of the aedeagal dorsal body and the aedeagal ventral ramus entirely wide with the inner margin sinuous. However, this species has the dorsal margin of the paramere sinuous, the apex of the basal bar not projected forward, and the apical margin of the aedeagal dorsal body wavy, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Azevedo, 2017" authorityName="Azevedo" authorityYear="2017" box="[1127,1246,1873,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Dissomphalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="urazius" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1127,1246,1873,1896]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">D. urazius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1254,1346,1871,1896]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1254,1346,1871,1896]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the dorsal margin of the paramere not sinuous, the apex of the basal bar projected forward and the apical margin of the aedeagal ventral ramus not wavy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
